HEADWORD: Oxidizer
<hw>Ox"i*di`zer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An agent employed in oxidation, or which facilitates or brings
about combination with oxygen; <as>as, nitric acid, chlorine, bromine,
etc., are strong <ex>oxidizers</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oxidulated</ent>⟦br⟧
